# Secure Containerized Application Deployment on AWS using ECS Fargate

A secure cloud-native deployment project demonstrating containerization, vulnerability scanning, and deployment of a Flask application on AWS using ECS Fargate.

---

# Project Overview

This project focuses on securely deploying a containerized Flask application using AWS cloud services and DevOps security practices.

The workflow includes:

- Docker containerization
- Vulnerability scanning using Trivy
- Secure image storage using Amazon ECR
- Deployment using Amazon ECS Fargate
- Monitoring using CloudWatch
- Secure networking using VPC and Security Groups

---

# Architecture

```text
Flask App
   ↓
Docker Container
   ↓
Trivy Vulnerability Scan
   ↓
Amazon ECR
   ↓
Amazon ECS Fargate
   ↓
Public Access
   ↓
CloudWatch Monitoring
```

---

# Technologies Used

| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Docker | Containerization |
| Python Flask | Web Application |
| Trivy | Vulnerability Scanning |
| Amazon ECR | Container Registry |
| Amazon ECS Fargate | Container Hosting |
| AWS VPC | Network Isolation |
| IAM | Access Control |
| CloudWatch | Logging & Monitoring |

---

# Features

- Secure Docker container deployment
- Vulnerability scanning with Trivy
- Hardened Docker image using Alpine Linux
- Non-root container execution
- AWS ECS Fargate deployment
- CloudWatch logging & monitoring
- Secure VPC and Security Group configuration

