# Project Structure

```text
project/
│
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
├── Dockerfile
├── .dockerignore
├── screenshots/
└── README.md
```

---

# Dockerfile (Secured)

```dockerfile
FROM python:3.12-alpine

WORKDIR /app

RUN adduser -D appuser

COPY requirements.txt .

RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

COPY . .

USER appuser

EXPOSE 5000

CMD ["python", "app.py"]
```

---

# Run Locally

## Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/solomanantony/Secure-Containerized-Application-Deployment-on-AWS-using-ECS-Fargate.git

cd Secure-Containerized-Application-Deployment-on-AWS-using-ECS-Fargate
```

---

## Build Docker Image

```bash
docker build -t secure-flask-app .
```

---

## Run Container

```bash
docker run -p 5000:5000 secure-flask-app
```

---

## Access Application

```text
http://localhost:5000
```

---

# Vulnerability Scanning with Trivy

## Scan Docker Image

```bash
trivy image secure-flask-app
```

---

# AWS Deployment Steps

1. Create Amazon ECR Repository
2. Push Docker Image to ECR
3. Create ECS Cluster
4. Create ECS Task Definition
5. Create ECS Service using Fargate
6. Configure VPC & Security Groups
7. Enable Public IP
8. Monitor logs using CloudWatch

